{
  "text": "The dynamical role of a stellar companion may equivalently be filled by the gravitational perturbation of a massive, distant perturbing planet well beyond Neptune's orbit [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ). This hy-pothesis has become more promising in light of growing evidence in support of the existence of such a planet Millholland & Laughin 2017; [CITATION_3] , however, the most recent estimates of the planet's orbit are insufficient to explain the Solar obliquity [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "121860384",
